title: For Sale/Trade:  CUSTOM 870 TACTICAL
postcontent:
Magpul 870P - upgrades make this one of the finest combat shotguns you could deploy in the defense of life, liberty, and the pursuit of happiness. 

It started as a Remington 870 Tactical - 18.5" threaded barrel with Tactical RemChoke muzzle stand-off/breaching device.  XS Sights picatinny rail with XS Sights rear Ghost Ring aperture and front XS Sights blade.  3" Magnum chambering and factory-installed +2 magazine extension makes this pack 7 full rounds of 2 3/4" shells or 6 3" Magnum shells.  

I then decided to add every available piece of Magpul SGA 870 furniture and accessories available: The Magpul SGA 870 stock, and forend.  In addition, I added the Magpul rear sling mount, which mounts between the receiver and stock and is ideal for connecting a single-point sling (Like the Magpul MS/2).  Also added is the front Magpul 870 sling attachment tower... which has a dual-sided connection.  One side has a fixed sling-attachment loop, the other has been enhanced with a heavy-duty, 1.25" QD Sling Swivel.  I have added a Blue Force Gear Larry Vickers digital camo QD/Qwik Adjustment sling.  This allows me to use this sling when I want or simply detach it and use the Magpul single-point sling when I want to, and gives a LOT of various ways to connect these slings and methods of carrying the shotgun... MANY MORE Than a simple strap most people use.  Also added the SGA 870 Stock riser kit for a bit extra "comb" for your cheek to rest on.  This makes using a red dot sight (like an Aimpoint etc.) much easier and very, very fast.  

-- I also purchased a precision-fit LimbSaver recoil pad and the Magpul stock adapter which allows the use of the LimbSaver with the stock.  The recoil reduction, less pain, and less muzzle climb and more controlability is absolutely dramatic.


After I got done upgrading all the externals I Set about making this gun the same as the 870P specifications and I upgraded and replaced each part found on the POLICE models.  I replaced the Extractor with the non-MIM (cast steel version vs the Express MIM-metal version) Extractor.  I then replaced the carrier latch spring which is heavier and stiffer for more positive feeding and enhanced results with full power loads.  I then installed the Wilson Combat heavy duty tactical magazine spring and follower, which is actually another improvement OVER the Police specifications.  I then also added the Wilson Combat oversized safety for perfect and positive manipulation when the situation is critical.  After careful discussion with a Remington certified factory and law enforcement armorer - I decided to leave the polymer trigger guard and sear spring alone.  The only thing the sear spring does is make the trigger pull stiffer and harder... Something police agencies may way (the idea being it's harder for the officer to pull the trigger so there is less chance of him shooting before he is absolutely wanting to shoot and a lawsuit will show the trigger was hard to pull etc) but certainly no civilian ... and the Polymer trigger guard is being looked at as actually much more durable and robust than the metal version sold in the Police models, so I kept it.

-- Hand polished the chamber with Dremel, felt, compound, wheels, etc.  Painstakingly slow and smooth work for absolutely enhanced extraction.

This is a build that has over $1,100 into it, just about as custom and piece by piece upgrading on a tactical / combat defense shotgun you could want or hope to get.    $750 or best offer

** Aimpoint Micro not included

The "J" was mis-stamped I'm assuming as it is visible lower than the WA. And in the right light, a "4" is visible..but again, that side is worn. P38 marking is very visible. Stitching is strong, no rips or tears. The holster is in very good condition. On the inside flap, some German I'm guessing inked "h 1242 (or it could be 1292) and what looks like "i". Spare mag pouch is solid. Comes with two era correct magazines. One is marked P38 on the side, JVD E/waA706 on the spine. The other is marked E/88 on the spine (near the bottom). No papers. title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Class (aka Concealed Carry Course) for $59
postcontent:
One of the requirements by the State of Florida to apply for a concealed weapons permit is to have successfully taken a concealed carry course under a certified instructor. Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.
